epgy ap physics p051 overview courses ohs summer schools apply and register home software research news contact epgy login course catalog physics ap level p051 mechanics lectures lessons exercises homework exams textbook epgy mechanics p051 systems of measurement motion in one dimension motion in two and three dimensions newton's laws work and energy systems of particles and the conservation of momentum rotation static equilibrium of a rigid body gravity oscillations the epgy mechanics course covers much of what is generally covered in a first semester college mechanics course the course prepares students to take the physics c mechanics ap exam the course is designed to take about 16 weeks to complete on average prerequisite calculus a or equivalent
